  "body": "## Summary\n- Fixed missing task templates for users with PostgreSQL-synced IDs  \n- Restored accurate chat unread badge counts for all user ID types  \n- Resolved cross-team reporting access for mixed ID-space environments  \n\n## Changes\n\n### Bug Fixes\n- **Task Creation** — Task templates now correctly appear in \"Everything\" creation mode for accounts synchronized with PostgreSQL IDs (pgId).  \n- **Chat** — Unread message badges now properly count all conversations, fixing an exclusion bug that affected users with Convex document IDs.  \n- **Team Reporting** — Restored access to cross-team reports when team identifiers are stored across different ID spaces (PostgreSQL vs. Convex).\n\n### Release Infrastructure\n- Improved Google Play upload stability with automatic retry logic for transient \"Edit has been deleted\" errors.\n\n## Technical Notes\n- **ID Normalization** — Migrated to centralized `userTeams` utilities (`getUserTeamIdSet`, `resolveCurrentUserIds`) to unify membership lookups across PostgreSQL (`pgId`) and Convex (`_id`) identifier spaces; replaced fragmented normalization logic in task creation, chat, and shared detail screens.  \n- **Data Integrity** — Eliminated silent `NaN` equality failures in chat unread-count logic by enforcing string-based ID comparisons.  \n- **Testing** — Added comprehensive unit tests for cross-space ID resolution and defensive null handling (`src/utils/userTeams.test.ts`).  \n- **Build** — Version bumped to 5.1.25 (Build 41); added `test:user-teams` npm script.  \n- **CI/CD** — Added 3-attempt retry logic with 5-second backoff for Google Play uploads; isolated edit lifecycle per attempt and ensured cleanup of orphaned edit sessions on failure.",
